title: Grateful Dead Live at Soldiers' and Sailors' Memorial Hall on 1979-12-11
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Loser, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, Easy To Love You, Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Shakedown Street-> Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Terrapin Station-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E:Alabama Getaway-> E: Promised Land

reviews.review_text: Quality audience tape 1979 audience tapes' quality are hit and miss, but this one is pretty good.  Nice to see the boys treated us to a China/Rider to close the first set; something usually saved for a set 2 opener.   Five songs from the then-upcoming Go To Heaven album.  I'd like to give this recording 4.5 stars, but the system won't allow it.  The Mason (jar) Taylor logo is clever.  Side note:  this show was about a month after my very first show, at the Nassau Coliseum in NY.  What a great ride the Dead gave us!,
Excellent Recording Upfront, deliciously warm and gooey tape. Best of the Mason Taylors I have heard.
Great Recording - The Mason Jar Althea!!  Love it!!

Unique Saint of Circumstance Great quality audience recording. Really feels like you are there.
My favorite track is the unique Saint of Circumstance with a slower lingering intro and by the end they flow it into a cool "Estimated Prophet"-esque jam.
